WEBVTT

00:00.552 --> 00:01.843
Previously on "The Originals"...

00:01.874 --> 00:04.045
If this prophecy is fulfilled,

00:04.075 --> 00:05.283
you will all fall...

00:05.313 --> 00:07.368
One by friend, one by foe,

00:07.398 --> 00:09.265
and one by family.

00:09.517 --> 00:11.422
When I am buried, the
family part of the prophecy

00:11.452 --> 00:12.356
will be over.

00:12.386 --> 00:14.291
Elijah, do it!

00:14.321 --> 00:16.622
Someone is ascending to the regency,

00:16.624 --> 00:19.992
the witch who was once
inhabited by Finn Mikaelson.

00:19.994 --> 00:22.149
They took it, the Serratura.

00:22.179 --> 00:24.596
The weapon that's used to
take down Klaus and Elijah?

00:24.598 --> 00:25.820
I was meeting with a witch.

00:25.850 --> 00:27.488
I was hoping she could help me destroy it.

00:27.518 --> 00:30.068
The only way to get
rid of it, is to use it.

00:30.070 --> 00:32.821
Do you actually love her?

00:33.941 --> 00:35.441
I've lost count of the amount of times

00:35.443 --> 00:37.238
you've been there for me.

00:39.947 --> 00:42.981
No. No!

00:46.270 --> 00:47.690
I think you're far more affected

00:47.720 --> 00:49.638
by this world than you care to admit.

00:49.640 --> 00:52.307
You want to control it rather than allow

00:52.309 --> 00:53.551
it to control you.

00:53.581 --> 00:56.762
The inevitable, unavoidable parts of life

00:56.764 --> 00:58.775
make you uneasy.

00:58.805 --> 01:02.333
No, no, no, no.

01:03.137 --> 01:05.683
Aah! Ugh!

01:05.912 --> 01:08.130
Some might say death is inevitable,

01:08.160 --> 01:10.760
and yet here I am a thousand years old,

01:10.790 --> 01:12.700
sipping an exquisite aged whiskey

01:12.730 --> 01:15.345
while a beguiling muse sits across from me.

01:15.375 --> 01:18.684
I am the perfect picture
of health and vitality,

01:18.686 --> 01:20.269
a master of my fate,

01:20.271 --> 01:22.821
a conqueror of death itself.

01:22.823 --> 01:26.046
Aah! Yaah!

01:26.076 --> 01:27.698
See? That's exactly my point.

01:27.728 --> 01:30.395
You make some glib,
throwaway line about death

01:30.397 --> 01:33.237
as though it means nothing
to you, but it does.

01:33.267 --> 01:35.689
If not your own, then at
least the death of others.

01:35.719 --> 01:37.858
So beneath the devilish banter

01:37.888 --> 01:39.304
and charming wit,

01:39.306 --> 01:41.159
Klaus Mikaelson bears the burden

01:41.189 --> 01:45.155
of a deep-seated psychological
trauma about death.

01:45.853 --> 01:47.252
Ragh!

01:47.282 --> 01:48.534
Ohh!

01:50.741 --> 01:52.986
I'll tell you what I
know about death, Camille.

01:53.016 --> 01:57.412
Death dances silently in everyone's shadow,

01:57.414 --> 02:00.878
And she doesn't give a damn, so...

02:01.441 --> 02:03.785
Why give a damn about her?

02:04.232 --> 02:06.233
You do give a damn.

02:07.007 --> 02:08.840
Why else surround yourself with immortals

02:08.842 --> 02:11.710
if not to avoid the agony of loss?

02:14.465 --> 02:17.516
You disagree. Fine.

02:17.518 --> 02:20.435
I hope it's a long time
before I'm proven right.

